==English==
===Etymology===
Eponym, [[w: Hans Gerhard Creutzfeldt]] and [[w:Alfons Maria Jakob]]
===Noun phrase===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Creutzfeldt-Jakob [[disease]]'''  (abbreviated as ''[[CJD]]'')
# {{pathology}} A [[rare]], [[progressive]],  currently [[fatal]] [[disease]] of the [[nervous system]], characterized by [[dementia]] and loss of [[muscle]] [[control]]. A [[prion]] disease, apparently transmissible from animals to humans by eating infected tissue, as well as from tissue interchanges among humans (corneal transplants, blood transfusions).

